    • Method Detail

      • evaluateLimit

        public LimitService.EvaluationResult evaluateLimit(LocalPlayer creator,
                                                   LocalWorld world,
                                                   Limit.Type type,
                                                   boolean evaluateParents)
        Evaluates whether the given creator exceeds limit on the given LocalWorld, testing against the given Limit.Type.
        Parameters:
        creator - the creator
        world - the LocalWorld
        type - the Limit.Type
        evaluateParents - Whether parents of the given type will be evaluated too (recursively). This is useful if not just a specific Limit.Type might be exceeded, but also a more general limit that includes the given one
        Returns:
        an EvaluationResult representing the result of the evaluation

      • getWarpsPerLimit

        public java.util.Map<Limit,java.util.List<Warp>> getWarpsPerLimit(LocalPlayer creator)
        Gets all warps created by the given player mapped under the applicable Limit.

        The map is guaranteed to include all limit that effect the given player. If no warp exists for a certain limit, get(Limit) will return an empty list.

        Parameters:
        creator - the creator
        Returns:
        a Map with all matching warps
